ext Step 2 Jun). Engaged and evaluative, not yet advocacy-driven.", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-21"}, {"name": "Joel", "risk": "Partner's advocacy depends on commercial terms (margin split, implementation scope, exclusivity). If partner terms are not aligned, Joel may stay neutral or advocate for a competitor where his firm has a stronger relationship or margin.", "role": "Influencer", "title": "Partner, Supply Chain Consulting", "sentiment": "Neutral to positive; partner is present on 21 May discovery call and engaged in pricing model discussion (Next Step 2 Jun: 'buyer-versus-Benelux-partner model and pricing approach to be worked through'). Asked about Zycus partner ecosystem role ('is there in your ecosystem a role to play for consultants like us?', 21 May). Potential advocate if partner pricing model is favorable.", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-21"}, {"name": "Jason", "risk": "If Jason is InfoSec/IT gatekeeper and his security concerns are not resolved, he can block or delay the deal at the technical workshop or contracting stage. Cloud-only vs on-prem objection is a known deal-killer for risk-averse buyers.", "role": "Influencer", "title": "Unknown (buyer-side, likely IT/InfoSec or digital transformation lead)", "sentiment": "Cautious; joined 21 May discovery call while driving, asked about dynamic OCR (AI interest), then raised on-prem deployment and security/geopolitical isolation concerns ('conversations are going back\u2026 isolate more\u2026 more like closed', 21 May). Likely IT/InfoSec gatekeeper. Concerns unresolved as of 26 Jun.", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-21"}, {"name": "Arthur Depoorter (Guus)", "risk": "Consultant role may be temporary (project-based); if Guus exits after finance ERP selection, Zycus loses an active evaluator and must rebuild relationship with Moore's internal team.", "role": "Evaluator", "title": "Senior Consultant - Supply Chain Consulting", "sentiment": "Engaged evaluator; requested capability map exchange ('Morgue to send